{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"It's a bit funny to be"},{"time":2000,"text":"at a conference dedicated to things not seen,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and present my proposal to build"},{"time":7000,"text":"a 6,000-kilometer-long wall"},{"time":9000,"text":"across the entire African continent."},{"time":12000,"text":"About the size of the Great Wall of China,"},{"time":15000,"text":"this would hardly be an invisible structure."},{"time":17000,"text":"And yet it's made from parts that are invisible, or near-invisible, to the naked eye:"},{"time":22000,"text":"bacteria and grains of sand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"Now, as architects we're trained to solve problems."},{"time":28000,"text":"But I don't really believe in architectural problems;"},{"time":30000,"text":"I only believe in opportunities."},{"time":32000,"text":"Which is why I'll show you a threat,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and an architectural response."},{"time":36000,"text":"The threat is desertification."},{"time":40000,"text":"My response is a sandstone wall"},{"time":43000,"text":"made from bacteria and solidified sand,"},{"time":45000,"text":"stretching across the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"Now, sand is a magical material"},{"time":51000,"text":"of beautiful contradictions."},{"time":53000,"text":"It is simple and complex."},{"time":56000,"text":"It is peaceful and violent."},{"time":58000,"text":"It is always the same, never the same,"},{"time":60000,"text":"endlessly fascinating."},{"time":62000,"text":"One billion grains of sand"},{"time":64000,"text":"come into existence in the world each second."},{"time":68000,"text":"That's a cyclical process."},{"time":70000,"text":"As rocks and mountains die,"},{"time":72000,"text":"grains of sand are born."},{"time":74000,"text":"Some of those grains may then cement naturally into sandstone."},{"time":77000,"text":"And as the sandstone weathers, new grains break free."},{"time":81000,"text":"Some of those grains may then accumulate"},{"time":83000,"text":"on a massive scale,"},{"time":85000,"text":"into a sand dune."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"In a way, the static, stone mountain"},{"time":91000,"text":"becomes a moving mountain of sand."},{"time":94000,"text":"But, moving mountains can be dangerous. Let me try and explain why."},{"time":98000,"text":"Dry areas cover more than one third of the Earth's land surfaces."},{"time":102000,"text":"Some are already deserts;"},{"time":104000,"text":"others are being seriously degraded by the sand."},{"time":107000,"text":"Just south of the Sahara we find the Sahel."},{"time":110000,"text":"The name means \"edge of the desert.\""},{"time":113000,"text":"And this is the region most closely associated with desertification."},{"time":117000,"text":"It was here in the late '60s and early '70s"},{"time":120000,"text":"that major droughts brought three million people"},{"time":123000,"text":"to become dependent upon emergency food aid,"},{"time":126000,"text":"with about up to 250,000 dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"This is a catastrophe waiting to happen again."},{"time":131000,"text":"And it's one that gets very little attention."},{"time":134000,"text":"In our accelerated media culture,"},{"time":136000,"text":"desertification is simply too slow"},{"time":139000,"text":"to reach the headlines."},{"time":141000,"text":"It's nothing like a tsunami or a Katrina:"},{"time":144000,"text":"too few crying children and smashed up houses."},{"time":149000,"text":"And yet desertification"},{"time":151000,"text":"is a major threat on all continents,"},{"time":153000,"text":"affecting some 110 countries"},{"time":156000,"text":"and about 70 percent of the world's agricultural drylands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"It seriously threatens the livelihoods"},{"time":165000,"text":"of millions of people,"},{"time":167000,"text":"and especially in Africa and China."},{"time":170000,"text":"And it is largely an issue that we've created for ourselves"},{"time":173000,"text":"through unsustainable use of scarce resources."},{"time":177000,"text":"So, we get climate change."},{"time":179000,"text":"We get droughts,"},{"time":180000,"text":"increased desertification,"},{"time":182000,"text":"crashing food systems, water scarcity,"},{"time":185000,"text":"famine, forced migration,"},{"time":189000,"text":"political instability, warfare, crisis."},{"time":193000,"text":"That's a potential scenario"},{"time":195000,"text":"if we fail to take this seriously."},{"time":197000,"text":"But, how far away is it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"I went to Sokoto in northern Nigeria"},{"time":201000,"text":"to try and find out how far away it is."},{"time":204000,"text":"The dunes here move southward at a pace of around 600 meters a year."},{"time":209000,"text":"That's the Sahara eating up almost [two meters] a day of the arable land,"},{"time":212000,"text":"physically pushing people away from their homes."},{"time":216000,"text":"Here I am -- I'm the second person on the left --"},{"time":219000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":221000,"text":"with the elders in Gidan-Kara,"},{"time":224000,"text":"a tiny village outside of Sokoto."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"They had to move this village in 1987"},{"time":229000,"text":"as a huge dune threatened to swallow it."},{"time":232000,"text":"So, they moved the entire village, hut by hut."},{"time":235000,"text":"This is where the village used to be."},{"time":237000,"text":"It took us about 10 minutes to climb up to the top of that dune,"},{"time":242000,"text":"which goes to show why they had to move to a safer location."},{"time":245000,"text":"That's the kind of forced migration"},{"time":247000,"text":"that desertification can lead to."},{"time":250000,"text":"If you happen to live close to the desert border,"},{"time":252000,"text":"you can pretty much calculate how long it will be"},{"time":254000,"text":"before you have to carry your kids away,"},{"time":256000,"text":"and abandon your home and your life as you know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"Now, sand dunes cover only about one fifth of our deserts."},{"time":265000,"text":"And still, those extreme environments are very good places"},{"time":268000,"text":"if we want to stop the shifting sands."},{"time":271000,"text":"Four years ago, 23 African countries"},{"time":274000,"text":"came together to create the Great Green Wall Sahara."},{"time":277000,"text":"A fantastic project, the initial plan"},{"time":280000,"text":"called for a shelter belt of trees to be planted"},{"time":282000,"text":"right across the African continent,"},{"time":284000,"text":"from Mauritania in the west, all the way to Djibouti in the east."},{"time":288000,"text":"If you want to stop a sand dune from moving,"},{"time":290000,"text":"what you need to make sure to do is to stop the grains"},{"time":292000,"text":"from avalanching over its crest."},{"time":295000,"text":"And a good way of doing that, the most efficient way,"},{"time":297000,"text":"is to use some kind of sand catcher."},{"time":299000,"text":"Trees or cacti are good for this."},{"time":302000,"text":"But, one of the problems with planting trees is that"},{"time":305000,"text":"the people in these regions are so poor"},{"time":307000,"text":"that they chop them down for firewood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"Now there is an alternative to just planting trees"},{"time":313000,"text":"and hoping that they won't get chopped down."},{"time":316000,"text":"This sandstone wall that I'm proposing essentially does three things."},{"time":319000,"text":"It adds roughness to the dune's surface,"},{"time":322000,"text":"to the texture of the dune's surface, binding the grains."},{"time":325000,"text":"It provides a physical support structure for the trees,"},{"time":328000,"text":"and it creates physical spaces,"},{"time":331000,"text":"habitable spaces inside of the sand dunes."},{"time":333000,"text":"If people live inside of the green barrier"},{"time":336000,"text":"they can help support the trees, protect them from humans,"},{"time":339000,"text":"and from some of the forces of nature."},{"time":341000,"text":"Inside of the dunes we find shade."},{"time":344000,"text":"We can start harvesting condensation,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and start greening the desert from within."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"Sand dunes are almost like ready-made buildings in a way."},{"time":352000,"text":"All we need to do is solidify the parts that we need to be solid,"},{"time":356000,"text":"and then excavate the sand,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and we have our architecture."},{"time":360000,"text":"We can either excavate it by hand"},{"time":362000,"text":"or we can have the wind excavate it for us."},{"time":364000,"text":"So, the wind carries the sand onto the site"},{"time":366000,"text":"and then it carries the redundant sand away from the structure for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"But, by now, you're probably asking,"},{"time":373000,"text":"how am I planning to solidify a sand dune?"},{"time":376000,"text":"How do we glue those grains of sand together?"},{"time":379000,"text":"And the answer is, perhaps, that you use these guys,"},{"time":382000,"text":"Bacillus pasteurii,"},{"time":384000,"text":"a micro-organism that is readily available in wetlands"},{"time":386000,"text":"and marshes, and does precisely that."},{"time":389000,"text":"It takes a pile of loose sand"},{"time":391000,"text":"and it creates sandstone out of it."},{"time":394000,"text":"These images from the American Society for Microbiology show us the process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"What happens is, you pour Bacillus pasteurii onto a pile of sand,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and it starts filling up the voids in between the grains."},{"time":405000,"text":"A chemical process produces calcite,"},{"time":407000,"text":"which is a kind of natural cement"},{"time":409000,"text":"that binds the grains together."},{"time":411000,"text":"The whole cementation process takes about 24 hours."},{"time":415000,"text":"I learned about this from a professor at U.C. Davis called Jason DeJong."},{"time":419000,"text":"He managed to do it in a mere 1,400 minutes."},{"time":423000,"text":"Here I am, playing the part of the mad scientist,"},{"time":425000,"text":"working with the bugs at UCL in London,"},{"time":429000,"text":"trying to solidify them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"So, how much would this cost?"},{"time":434000,"text":"I'm not an economist, very much not,"},{"time":436000,"text":"but I did, quite literally, a back of the envelope calculation --"},{"time":440000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":442000,"text":"-- and it seems that for a cubic meter of concrete"},{"time":445000,"text":"we would have to pay in the region of 90 dollars."},{"time":448000,"text":"And, after an initial cost of 60 bucks to buy the bacteria,"},{"time":451000,"text":"which you'll never have to pay again,"},{"time":453000,"text":"one cubic meter of bacterial sand"},{"time":456000,"text":"would be about 11 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458000,"text":"How do we construct something like this?"},{"time":460000,"text":"Well, I'll quickly show you two options."},{"time":462000,"text":"The first is to create a kind of balloon structure,"},{"time":464000,"text":"fill it with bacteria, then allow the sand to wash over the balloon,"},{"time":468000,"text":"pop the balloon, as it were, disseminating the bacteria into the sand and solidifying it."},{"time":472000,"text":"Then, a few years afterwards,"},{"time":474000,"text":"using permacultural strategies,"},{"time":476000,"text":"we green that part of the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"The second alternative would be to use injection piles."},{"time":482000,"text":"So, we pushed the piles down through the dune,"},{"time":484000,"text":"and we create an initial bacterial surface."},{"time":487000,"text":"We then pull the piles up through the dune"},{"time":490000,"text":"and we're able to create almost any conceivable shape inside of the sand"},{"time":493000,"text":"with the sand acting as a mold as we go up."},{"time":497000,"text":"So, we have a way of turning sand into sandstone,"},{"time":501000,"text":"and then creating these habitable spaces inside of the desert dunes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505000,"text":"But, what should they look like?"},{"time":507000,"text":"Well, I was inspired, for my architectural form, by tafoni,"},{"time":512000,"text":"which look a little bit like this, this is a model representation of it."},{"time":515000,"text":"These are cavernous rock structures that I found on the site in Sokoto."},{"time":518000,"text":"And I realized that if I scaled them up, they would provide me"},{"time":521000,"text":"with good spatial qualities,"},{"time":524000,"text":"for ventilation, for thermal comfort, and for other things."},{"time":527000,"text":"Now, part of the formal control over this structure"},{"time":530000,"text":"would be lost to nature, obviously,"},{"time":532000,"text":"as the bacteria do their work."},{"time":535000,"text":"And I think this creates a kind of boundless beauty actually."},{"time":538000,"text":"I think there is really something in that articulation"},{"time":541000,"text":"that is quite nice."},{"time":543000,"text":"We see the result, the traces, if you like,"},{"time":547000,"text":"of the Bacillus pasteurii being harnessed to sculpt the desert"},{"time":550000,"text":"into these habitable environments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"Some people believe that"},{"time":555000,"text":"this would spread uncontrollably,"},{"time":557000,"text":"and that the bacteria would kill everything in its way."},{"time":559000,"text":"That's not true at all."},{"time":561000,"text":"It's a natural process. It goes on in nature today,"},{"time":563000,"text":"and the bacteria die as soon as we stop feeding them."},{"time":566000,"text":"So, there it is --"},{"time":568000,"text":"architectural anti-desertification structures"},{"time":571000,"text":"made from the desert itself."},{"time":573000,"text":"Sand-stopping devices, made from sand."},{"time":577000,"text":"The world is likely to lose one third of its arable land"},{"time":580000,"text":"by the end of the century."},{"time":582000,"text":"In a period of unprecedented population growth"},{"time":586000,"text":"and increased food demands, this could prove disastrous."},{"time":588000,"text":"And quite frankly, we're putting our heads in the sand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"If nothing else, I would like for this scheme to initiate a discussion."},{"time":597000,"text":"But, if I had something like a TED wish,"},{"time":599000,"text":"it would be to actually get it built,"},{"time":601000,"text":"to start building this habitable wall,"},{"time":604000,"text":"this very, very long, but very narrow city in the desert,"},{"time":608000,"text":"built into the dunescape itself."},{"time":612000,"text":"It's not only something that supports trees,"},{"time":615000,"text":"but something that connects people and countries together."},{"time":619000,"text":"I would like to conclude by showing you an animation of the structure,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and leave you with a sentence by Jorge Luis Borges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"Borges said that \"nothing is built on stone,"},{"time":637000,"text":"everything is built on sand,"},{"time":641000,"text":"but we must build as if the sand were stone.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"Now, there are many details left to explore in this scheme --"},{"time":650000,"text":"political, practical, ethical, financial."},{"time":655000,"text":"My design, as it takes you down the rabbit hole,"},{"time":660000,"text":"is fraught with many challenges"},{"time":664000,"text":"and difficulties in the real world."},{"time":667000,"text":"But, it's a beginning, it's a vision."},{"time":671000,"text":"As Borges would have it, it's the sand."},{"time":675000,"text":"And I think now is really the time"},{"time":678000,"text":"to turn it into stone. Thank you."},{"time":681000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}